OL,6,FAdam Dickson, project curator, said:
OL,7,F"The Ellisland collection is hugely
OL,8,Fimportant, but it's under threat from
OL,9,Fenvironmental conditions that make
OL,10,Fproper care impossible. The Barnbougle
OL,11,FPapers, for example, have given us
OL,12,Funprecedented insight into how Burns
OL,13,Ffurnished his home and managed his
OL,14,Ffarm.
OL,16,F"Creating a dedicated museum space
OL,17,Fwill deepen our understanding of
OL,18,FBurns's creative process and his life
OL,19,Fwith Jean and their family at
OL,20,FEllisland."
